INSERT INTO `news` VALUES ('0081f88d-17fa-47e6-992b-a9e77e9a31ad','d6de5dd8-df98-43dd-96a7-b3b9b713b62a','Fifth Season of \'Ani ni Tsukeru Kusuri wa Nai!\' Announced','2022-07-13 11:52:48','2022-07-13 11:52:48','62ceb21022fb8.jpeg','<p>The official website for the <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/anime/35015/\">anime adaptation</a> of <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/44612/\">Ling You</a>\'s web manhua series <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/manga/104937/\">Ani ni Tsukeru Kusuri wa Nai!</a> (Please Take My Brother Away) announced on Wednesday that the <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/anime/49599/\">fifth season</a> will premiere on the d Anime Store platform in Japan on July 29. The season began airing in China on the Tencent streaming service on June 29.<br><br>Cast members from the previous seasons will reprise their respective roles. <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/22351/\">Rareko</a> (Aggressive Retsuko (ONA)) is returning as the director and scriptwriter. <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/anime/producer/1690/\">Imagineer</a> and <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/anime/producer/1727/\">Tencent Penguin Pictures</a> are producing the anime, with the latter also credited for production.<br><br>The first season aired in 12 three-minute episodes in Spring 2017, followed by three more seasons in Summer 2018, Fall 2019, and Fall 2020.</p>'),('1781e96e-bfe8-4526-a485-96f8c0d9edd9','b13e7a92-429f-4049-8985-fb1abbfa4161','\'RPG Fudousan\' Reveals Supporting Cast Members','2022-07-13 13:32:06','2022-07-13 13:32:06','62cec9564edbe.jpeg','<p>The <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/anime/48363/\">RPG Fudousan</a> (RPG Real Estate) special stage at AnimeJapan 2022 revealed on Sunday three additional cast and its second key visual (pictured). The anime is scheduled to premiere on April 6 at 9:30 p.m. on AT-X, followed by Tokyo MX, TV Aichi, KBS Kyoto, Sun TV, and BS Nittele.<br><br>Cast<br>Satna: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/7263/\">Youko Hikasa</a> (Arifureta Shokugyou de Sekai Saikyou)<br>Sarah: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/22003/\">Minami Takahashi</a> (Sentouin, Hakenshimasu!)<br>Mona: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/42508/\">Honoka Kuroki</a> (Centaur no Nayami)<br><br><a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/47717/\">Tomoaki Koshida</a> (Sewayaki Kitsune no Senko-san) helms the anime at <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/anime/producer/95/\">Doga Kobo</a>. <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/36760/\">Yoshiko Nakamura</a> (Maoujou de Oyasumi) is handling the series composition, and <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/34549/\">Motohiro Taniguchi</a> (Yuru Yuri San☆Hai!) is designing the characters.<br><br>The anime adapts <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/12949/\">Chiyo Kenmotsu</a>\'s 4-koma <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/manga/134223/\">slice of life fantasy manga</a>, which began serializing irregularly in <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/manga/magazine/361/\">Manga Time Kirara Carat</a> magazine from April to June 2018 before joining the magazine\'s regular lineup the following month. Houbunsha shipped the fourth volume on April 27.</p>'),('1b8719c8-01ab-42fd-ac4b-a22e7b36afec','b13e7a92-429f-4049-8985-fb1abbfa4161','\'Tomodachi Game\' Unveils Additional Cast, First Promo','2022-07-15 09:59:54','2022-07-15 09:59:54','62d13a9ae166e.jpeg','<p>The official website of the Tomodachi Game (Friends Game) television anime revealed on Tuesday three additional cast members and the first promotional video. The anime is scheduled to premiere on April 6 at 1:29 a.m. on NTV, followed by BS NTV, and AT-X.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Cast</p><p>Manabu-kun: Minami Takayama (Detective Conan)</p><p>Maria Minase: Reina Ueda (Darwin\'s Game)</p><p>Tsukino: Shizuka Itou (Highschool DxD)</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Nana Mizuki (Shaman King (2021)) performs the opening theme \"Double Shuffle,\" which is previewed in the promotional video below. J-rock band saji (Ahiru no Sora) is performing the ending theme \"Tomoshibi.\"</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Hirofumi Ogura (Kuroshitsuji II) is helming the anime at animation studio Okuruto Noboru. Kenta Ihara (Youjo Senki) is handling the series composition and script. Satomi Miyazaki (Shingeki no Kyoujin animation director) is designing the characters and Michiru (7 Seeds) is composing the music.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The anime adapts Mikoto Yamaguchi and Yuuki Satou\'s psychological survival manga, which began in Bessatsu Shounen Magazine in December 2013. Kodansha shipped the 19th volume on November 9.</p>'),('264fe8df-84ad-480e-a196-10129ea45096','d6de5dd8-df98-43dd-96a7-b3b9b713b62a','Manga \'Shangri-La Frontier: Kusoge Hunter, Kamige ni Idoman to su\' Gets TV Anime in 2023','2022-07-13 10:52:13','2022-07-13 11:57:55','62ceb3432c44d.jpeg','<p>Publisher Kodansha opened an official website for a television anime adaptation of <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/52294/\">Katarina</a> and <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/38443/\">Ryousuke Fuji</a>\'s <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/manga/130331/\">Shangri-La Frontier: Kusoge Hunter, Kamige ni Idoman to su</a> (Shangri-La Frontier) manga on Thursday. The website revealed the main cast, staff, teaser visual (pictured), and project promotional video. The anime is scheduled to premiere in 2023.<br><br>Cast<br>Sunraku (Rakurou Hizutome): <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/33995/\">Yuuma Uchida</a> (Jujutsu Kaisen (TV))<br>Psyger 0 (Rei Saiga): <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/36812/\">Azumi Waki</a> (Isekai Maou to Shoukan Shoujo no Dorei Majutsu)<br>Arthur Pencilgon (Towa Amane): <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/7263/\">Youko Hikasa</a> (RWBY: Hyousetsu Teikoku)<br>Oicazzo (Kei Uomi): <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/39366/\">Makoto Koichi</a> (100-man no Inochi no Ue ni Ore wa Tatteiru)<br>Emul: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/5250/\">Rina Hidaka</a> (Tate no Yuusha no Nariagari)<br>Viceash: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/146/\">Akio Ootsuka</a> (Beastars)<br><br>Staff<br>Director: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/12701/\">Toshiyuki Kubooka</a> (Majo no Tabitabi)<br>Series Composition, Script: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/15641/\">Kazuyuki Fudeyasu</a> (Tensei shitara Slime Datta Ken)<br>Assistant Director: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/50462/\">Hiroki Ikeshita</a> (Hitoribocchi no Marumaru Seikatsu)<br>Character Design, Chief Animation Director: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/38096/\">Ayumi Kurashima</a> (Devilman: Crybaby)<br>Action &amp; Special Effects Director: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/41466/\">Satoshi Sakai</a> (Shingeki no Kyojin: The Final Season)<br>Color Design: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/33793/\">Masato Takagi</a> (Tsuki ga Michibiku Isekai Douchuu)<br>Art: <a href=\"http://www.inspired.jp/\">Inspired</a> (Kemono Jihen)<br>2D Works: Azusa Tamura (Koi wa Ameagari no You ni)\\<br>Director of Photography: Hikaru Yamamoku (Araburu Kisetsu no Otome-domo yo. photography)<br>Editing: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/38890/\">Gou Sadamatsu</a> (Golden Kamuy)<br>Sound Director: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/35673/\">Akiko Fujita</a> (Dorohedoro)<br>Music: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/15481/\">MONACA</a> (Assassins Pride)<br>Studio: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/anime/producer/605/\">C2C</a><br><br>Katarina began writing the series as a web novel on the Shousetsuka ni Narou website in May 2017. Fuji started to adapt the story into a manga in <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/manga/magazine/8/\">Weekly Shounen Magazine</a> in July 2020. Kodansha shipped the eighth volume on April 15, while the ninth volume is scheduled to release on July 15.<br><br>Kodansha USA <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/news/64487327\">licensed</a> the manga digitally in English in November 2020 and released the sixth volume on May 3.<br><br>Shangri-La Frontier was <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/news/66359929\">nominated</a> at the 46th Kodansha Manga Awards in the Shounen category.<br><br>Synopsis<br>Second-year high school student Rakurou Hizutome is interested in one thing only: finding \"shitty games\" and beating the crap out of them. His gaming skills are second to none, and no game is too bad for him to enjoy. So when he\'s introduced to the new VR game Shangri-La Frontier, he does what he does best—min-maxes and skips the prologue to jump straight into the action. But can even an expert gamer like Rakurou discover all the secrets that Shangri-La Frontier hides...? (Source: Kodansha USA)</p>'),('28bafb5d-22fa-40fe-9a55-05fbde36b671','d6de5dd8-df98-43dd-96a7-b3b9b713b62a','Manhwa \'The Reason Why Raeliana Ended up at the Duke\'s Mansion\' Gets TV Anime','2022-07-13 12:26:51','2022-07-13 12:26:51','62ceba0b24b08.jpeg','<p>An official website for a television anime adaptation of <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/49613/\">Milcha</a> and <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/49656/\">Gorae</a>\'s <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/manga/118646/\">The Reason Why Raeliana Ended up at the Duke\'s Mansion</a> manhwa opened on Monday. The website revealed the first key visual (pictured).<br><br>Milcha and Gorae serialized the fantasy romance manwha in <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/manga/magazine/1439/\">Kakao</a> website from September 2017 to March last year and released it physically into 7 volumes. Kadokawa published the manhwa in Japan and shipped the seventh and final volume on July 5.<br><br>Yen Press <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/news/64487327\">licensed</a> the manhwa in English on October 8. The first volume was released on June 22 while the second volume is scheduled to ship on October 18. The manhwa is also released digitally on the Tappytoon webtoon site.<br><br>Synopsys<br>When Park Eunha dies in modern-day Korea, she awakens in the body of Raeliana McMillan, the eldest daughter of a nouveaux riche baron. However, this is no ordinary world; it\'s the exact same one as a novel she once read. Beloved by her family, it would seem as though she is in a fairy tale. But Raeliana is far from the main character—she is a mere plot device, whose murder at the hands of her fiancé instigates the entire story.<br><br>Raeliana has no intention to accept her fate quietly. She sets her eyes on someone in a position of great power—the vieux riche male protagonist Duke Noah Volstaire Wynknight—aiming to completely change the original story. Using her knowledge of future events, Raeliana offers information to Noah on the condition that he acts as her fake fiancé, but the Duke\'s two-faced nature throws a wrench in her plans! [Written by MAL Rewrite]</p>'),('2e71406f-d7ec-41be-94e3-1bd5d120b83d','d9d5bb12-6d6d-478d-adcc-38cac4bd488c','\'Yuru Yuri Nachuyachumi!+\' TV Specials To Air this Summer, \'San☆Hai!\' in Fall','2022-07-15 10:27:06','2022-07-15 10:27:06','62d140fa859b0.jpg','<p>Yuru Yuri\'s original creator, Namori, announced on her official Twitter that the Yuru Yuri Nachuyachumi! OVA will be broadcast on TV in July. Two new episodes, titled Yuru Yuri Nachuyachumi!+, will then be broadcast on TV in August and September.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>These three episodes will lead up to the previously announced third season, Yuru Yuri San☆Hai!, which will begin airing in October.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Yuru Yuri Nachuyachumi! previewed at screenings in theaters in November 2014, and was released on DVD and Blu-ray format in February 2015. The first season of Yuru Yuri aired in 2011 and received a sequel in 2012, each completing at 12 episodes.</p>'),('3f5c9e69-67d0-4001-9a85-0ae21904528b','b13e7a92-429f-4049-8985-fb1abbfa4161','\'Gaikotsu Kishi-sama, Tadaima Isekai e Odekakechuu\' Reveals Additional Cast, Third Promo','2022-07-15 09:50:34','2022-07-15 09:50:34','62d13869b3b35.jpeg','<p>The official website of the Gaikotsu Kishi-sama, Tadaima Isekai e Odekakechuu (Skeleton Knight in Another World) television anime revealed on Friday five additional cast and a third promotional video. The anime is scheduled to premiere on April 7 at 11:30 p.m. on AT-X, followed by Tokyo MX, Sun TV, and BS11.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Cast</p><p>Sect: Kengo Kawanishi (Dr. Stone)</p><p>Dacares: Daiki Hamano (Darling in the FranXX)</p><p>Juliana: Saori Oonishi (Arifureta Shokugyou de Sekai Saikyou)</p><p>Domitian: Akira Ishida (Kimetsu no Yaiba)</p><p>Setrion: Minoru Shiraishi (Hajimete no Gal)</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Anisong unit Dialogue+ (Hige wo Soru. Soshite Joshikousei wo Hirou.) is performing the ending theme \"Bokura ga Orokadanante Dare ga Itta,\" which is previewed in the promotional video below.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Katsumi Ono (Senki Zesshou Symphogear G) is helming the anime at animation studios HORNETS and Studio Kai. Takeshi Kikuchi (Night Wizard original creator) is handling the series composition and Tooru Imanishi (Shuumatsu Nani Shitemasu ka? Isogashii Desu ka? Sukutte Moratte Ii Desu ka?) is designing the characters. Eba (Wizard Barristers: Benmashi Cecil opening theme composition) and Tsubasa Itou (Princess Connect! Re:Dive) are composing the music.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The anime adapts Enki Hakari\'s action fantasy novel, which began on the Shousetsuka ni Narou website in October 2014. Overlap began publishing the series featuring illustrations by KeG the following June and published the ninth volume in March 2019.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Akira Sawano began drawing a manga adaptation on Overlap\'s Comic Gardo web manga portal in February 2017. The ninth volume shipped on September 25.</p><p>Seven Seas Entertainment licensed both light novels and manga in English in September 2018. The light novel\'s ninth volume shipped digitally on May 27 and physically on August 3. The manga\'s eighth volume will ship on April 26.</p>'),('4f851d84-2175-463f-87fa-387e99f308ee','d6de5dd8-df98-43dd-96a7-b3b9b713b62a','Panty & Stocking with Garterbelt\' TV Anime Gets New Anime Project','2022-07-13 12:31:50','2022-07-13 12:31:50','62cebb36e921d.jpeg','<p>The <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/anime/producer/803/\">Trigger</a> 10 Year Anniversary &amp; Announcement Panel announced on Saturday that a second season of <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/anime/8795/\">Panty &amp; Stocking with Garterbelt</a> animated by Trigger is in production.<br><br>Animation studio <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/anime/producer/6/\">Gainax</a> produced the 13-episode first season and aired in Fall 2010. Funimation streamed the anime with subtitles and an English dub. The company released a DVD set in July 2012 and Blu-Ray in January 2013.<br><br>The \"Anarchy Sisters,\" Panty and Stocking, have been kicked out of Heaven for, to put it mildly, misbehaving. Led by a priest named Garterbelt, these angels must buy their way back by exterminating ghosts in Daten City. But this task requires unconventional weapons for these unorthodox angels—they transform their lingerie into weapons to dispatch the spirits. Unfortunately, neither of them take their duties seriously, as they rather spend their time in pursuit of other \"hobbies\": Panty prefers to sleep with anything that walks, and Stocking favors stuffing her face with sweets than hunting ghosts.<br><br>Follow these two unruly angels as they battle ghosts, an overflow of bodily fluids, and their own tendency to get side-tracked in Panty &amp; Stocking with Garterbelt. [Written by MAL Rewrite]</p>'),('53c9600b-1f6b-45c8-a6f3-5f50bdef3913','d6de5dd8-df98-43dd-96a7-b3b9b713b62a','Fifth Season of \'Date A Live\' Announced','2022-07-13 11:03:11','2022-07-13 11:59:15','62ceb393958e9.jpeg','<p>The 12th and final episode of the <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/anime/41461/\">Date A Live IV</a> television anime announced on Saturday that a fifth season is in production. The new season will air under the title Date A Live V.<br><br>The anime series adapts <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/16861/\">Koushi Tachibana</a>\'s <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/manga/37523/\">sci-fi romance light novel</a>, which began publishing under the Fujimi Fantasia Bunko label in March 2011, featuring illustrations by <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/16991/\">Tsunako</a>. Fujimi Shobo published the 22nd and final volume in March 2020. Date A Live has a cumulative 6 million copies of its compiled volumes in circulation.<br><br><a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/anime/producer/292/\">AIC Plus+</a> produced the <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/anime/15583/\">first anime season</a> in Spring 2013. The <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/anime/19163/\">second season</a> by <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/anime/producer/1053/\">Production IMS</a> premiered in 10 episodes the following Spring. The <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/anime/24655/\">Date A Live: Mayuri Judgment</a> anime film screened in Japan in August 2015. <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/anime/producer/7/\">J.C.Staff</a> produced the <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/anime/36633/\">third season</a>, which aired in Winter 2019.<br><br>The fourth season by <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/anime/producer/1857/\">GEEK TOYS</a> premiered on April 8. The animation studio also produced the two-part <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/anime.php?cat=anime&amp;q=Date+A+Bullet&amp;type=3&amp;p=1857\">Date A Bullet</a> spin-off movie, which opened in theaters in August and November 2020.</p>'),('5d1ad9f1-d89d-455f-b68c-885484ecf25a','b13e7a92-429f-4049-8985-fb1abbfa4161','\'Shokei Shoujo no Virgin Road\' Announces Additional Cast','2022-07-15 10:02:23','2022-07-15 10:02:23','62d13b2f9d90f.jpeg','<p>The official website for the television anime adaptation of Mato Satou\'s Shokei Shoujo no Virgin Road (The Executioner and Her Way of Life) light novel revealed three additional cast members on Sunday. The anime is scheduled to premiere on April 2 at 1:30 a.m. on Tokyo MX and BS11, followed by AT-X.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Cast</p><p>Mitsuki: Yuuma Uchida (Scarlet Nexus)</p><p>Flare: Yuuko Kaida (The God of High School)</p><p>Orwell: Tamie Kubota (Selector Infected WIXOSS)</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Yoshiki Kawasaki (Honzuki no Gekokujou assistant director) is helming the anime at J.C.Staff, with Shougo Yasukawa (Nejimaki Seirei Senki: Tenkyou no Alderamin) handling the series composition. Keiko Tamaki (Hataraku Saibou!! sub-character design) is in charge of the character designs and Michiru (Given) composes the music.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Satou originally launched the light novel on the Shousetsuka ni Narou website before SB creative began publishing it through its GA Bunko imprint in July 2019, featuring illustrations by Nilitsu. The sixth volume shipped on August 15. Yen Press licensed the light novel in English in September 2020 and will ship the fourth volume on April 19.</p>'),('752ce3b6-f7ae-4761-b2a4-0285951c97e3','d9d5bb12-6d6d-478d-adcc-38cac4bd488c','\'Noragami\' and \'Nanatsu no Taizai\' Manga Bundle New OVAs','2022-07-15 10:28:13','2022-07-15 10:28:13','62d1413d888a6.jpg','<p>It has been announced that upcoming manga volumes of Noragami and Nanatsu no Taizai will bundle new anime discs.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Noragami has two OVAs planned, to be bundled with the 15th and 16th manga volumes on November 17, 2015 and March 17, 2016, respectively. The first will feature the chapter, Nijikan no Teikei ni So Koto (Following A Stereotypical Two Hours), from the spin-off series Noragami: Shuuishuu (pictured right). The second will be based on the 41st chapter of the manga, where the main characters pay a visit to Capyper Land. Previously, a 2-episode OVA was released in 2014. The first episode adapted the 25th chapter of the manga, and the second episode adapted the cherry blossom-viewing arc.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Nanatsu no Taizai\'s new OVA will be bundled with the upcoming 16th volume of the manga, to be released on August 12. The anime disc will feature side stories of the main characters in omnibus format. An OVA episode featuring the sin of greed, Nanatsu no Taizai: Ban no Bangai-hen, was previously announced to be bundled with the manga\'s 15th volume. It will be released on June 17.</p>'),('779988e3-06ac-475f-bbe8-fd576be92487','b13e7a92-429f-4049-8985-fb1abbfa4161','\'Kono Healer, Mendokusai\' Announces Additional Cast','2022-07-13 13:22:29','2022-07-13 13:22:59','62cec71516353.jpeg','<p>The official website of the <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/anime/48742/\">Kono Healer, Mendokusai</a> (Don\'t Hurt Me, My Healer!) television anime revealed 20 additional cast members and the opening theme on Monday. The anime premiered on AT-X on April 10 at 9:00 p.m., followed by Tokyo MX, BS11, and Kantele.<br><br>Cast<br>Beast: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/22195/\">Chado Horii</a> (Genei wo Kakeru Taiyou)<br>Gobkichi: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/14425/\">Hina Sakurai</a> (Viper\'s Creed)<br>Cyclops: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/45495/\">Tarou Kiuchi</a> (BNA)<br>Orc: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/7512/\">Kenji Akabane</a> (Magi: The Kingdom of Magic)<br>Witch: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/80/\">Aya Hisakawa</a> (Kyousou Giga (TV))<br>Thief: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/11622/\">Ayane Sakura</a> (Maoujou de Oyasumi)<br>Golem: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/395/\">Tetsu Inada</a> (Maou Gakuin no Futekigousha: Shijou Saikyou no Maou no Shiso, Tensei shite Shison-tachi no Gakkou e Kayou)<br>Zombies: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/38438/\">Kouhei Amasaki</a> (Re:Zero kara Hajimeru Isekai Seikatsu)<br>Ellie: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/46817/\">Hiyori Kouno</a> (Death March kara Hajimaru Isekai Kyousoukyoku)<br>Dryad: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/211/\">Saori Gotou</a> (Fairy Tail: Final Series)<br>Medusa: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/49032/\">Yuuko Natsuyoshi</a> (Kenja no Deshi wo Nanoru Kenja)<br>Brigan: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/2/\">Tomokazu Sugita</a> (Goblin Slayer)<br>Anna: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/9593/\">Mai Fuchigami</a> (Outbreak Company)<br>Ryoko: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/21543/\">Yumiri Hanamori</a> (Shinchou Yuusha: Kono Yuusha ga Ore Tueee Kuse ni Shinchou Sugiru)<br>Receptionist: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/35441/\">Marika Kouno</a> (Kami-tachi ni Hirowareta Otoko)<br>Mimic: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/222/\">Ayaka Saitou</a> (Jewelpet)<br>Celia: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/30901/\">Maria Naganawa</a> (Kobayashi-san Chi no Maid Dragon)<br>Cyclops Lady: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/19884/\">Saori Oonishi</a> (Monster Musume no Iru Nichijou)<br>Brigun: Chado Horii<br>Brigin: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/6724/\">Gou Shinomiya</a> (Ao no Exorcist: Kyoto Fujouou-hen)<br>Mayor: Yuki Tamai<br><br><a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/48883/\">Nobuaki Nakanishi</a> (Mahoujin Guruguru) helms the anime at animation studio <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/anime/producer/755/\">Jumondo</a>. <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/8067/\">Fumihiko Shimo</a> (Dumbbell Nan Kilo Moteru?) is penning the script and handling the series composition.<a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/38757/\">Chisato Kikunaga</a> (Koisuru Asteroid chief animation director) is designing the characters.<br><br>The anime adapts <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/50990/\">Tannen ni Hakkou</a>\'s comedy-fantasy<a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/manga/125180/\"> manga</a>, which began serializing on the <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/manga/magazine/1159/\">ComicWalker</a> web manga portal in July 2019. Kadokawa will ship the fifth volume on April 22.</p>'),('86efe033-2751-4c22-8d2d-afa7aaa4f23c','d9d5bb12-6d6d-478d-adcc-38cac4bd488c','Broadcast Premiere of \'God Eater\' Delayed by One Week','2022-07-15 10:25:23','2022-07-15 10:25:23','62d14093174de.jpg','<p>God Eater, originally scheduled to premiere on July 5, will be postponed by one week, according to an announcement on the official website. A special program titled God Eater Extra will air in the time slot instead of the first episode. The announcement reasoned that the project staff wanted to deliver a work quality that meets fan expectations.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>An early screening of the first episode, originally scheduled for June 28 at Akihabara UDX, had been canceled last week. That episode is also scheduled for screening on the third day of Anime Expo 2015 in Los Angeles this weekend, but that is unlikely to occur.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>God Eater is based on an action role-playing game of the same name released in 2010 on PlayStation Portable. Its adaptation is being animated by ufotable.</p>'),('89d5ebc4-9aea-4c9f-bcf6-bc0590e820a5','b13e7a92-429f-4049-8985-fb1abbfa4161','\'Love All Play\' Announces Pair of Cast','2022-07-13 13:24:09','2022-07-13 13:24:09','62cec779136c5.jpeg','<p>The official website of the <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/anime/49556/\">Love All Play</a> television anime revealed two supporting cast members on Friday. The anime premiered on April 2 at 5:30 p.m. on NTV and Yomiuri TV.<br><br>Cast<br>Kenjin Yusa: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/196/\">Kishou Taniyama</a> (Ahiru no Sora)<br>Yuusuke Yokokawa: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/64/\">Hiroki Takahashi</a> (Tennis no Ouji-sama)<br><br><a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/29285/\">Hiroshi Takeuchi</a> (Blade &amp; Soul) is helming the anime at <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/anime/producer/22/\">Nippon Animation</a> and <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/anime/producer/28/\">OLM</a>. <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/8462/\">Tomoko Konparu</a> (Ao Haru Ride) is handling the series composition and is penning the script with <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/30221/\">Miharu Hirami</a> (Handa-kun), <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/26493/\">Shingo Irie</a> (Hinomaruzumou), and <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/2096/\">Michiko Yokote</a> (Tsurune: Kazemai Koukou Kyuudoubu). <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/55053/\">Riko Kaneda</a> (Yakunara Mug Cup mo animation director) is designing the characters and <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/21495/\">Yuki Hayashi</a> (Bakuten!!) is composing the music.<br><br>The anime adapts <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/55054/\">Asami Koseki</a>\'s badminton novel, which had its first novel shipped under Poplar\'s Pureful imprint in May 2011. The fourth and latest novel was released in March 2014. A new edition of the novel released on August 25.<br><br><a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/anime/producer/1365/\">Shueisha</a> will begin serializing a manga adaptation of Love All Play on with art by Dam Miyata in their Tonari no Young Jump magazine on April 8.</p>'),('94c1cd63-995c-4e12-92ea-505758bb54c2','d6de5dd8-df98-43dd-96a7-b3b9b713b62a','Manga \'Mashle\' Gets TV Anime in 2023','2022-07-13 10:55:59','2022-07-13 12:09:32','62ceb5fc0268e.jpeg','<p>Aniplex announced on Monday a television anime adaptation of <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/50439/\">Hajime Koumoto</a>\'s <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/manga/124085/\">Mashle</a> (Mashle: Magic &amp; Muscles). The company also opened an official website revealing a teaser visual (pictured) and an announcement video. The anime is scheduled to premiere in 2023.<br><br>Koumoto began serializing the action-comedy manga in <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/manga/magazine/83/\">Weekly Shounen Jump</a> magazine in January 2020. Shueisha shipped the 12th volume on July 4. Mashle has a cumulative 3 million copies of its compiled volumes worldwide.<br><br>VIZ Media licensed the manga in English in October 2020. The sixth volume was released on May 17 and the seventh volume is scheduled to ship on July 19. Mashle is also sims published on the MANGA Plus website.<br><br>Synopsis<br>To everyone else in his magic-dominated world, the young and powerless Mash Burnedead is a threat to the gene pool and must be purged. Living secretly in the forest, he spends every day training his body, building muscles strong enough to compete with magic itself! However, upon having his identity exposed and his peaceful life threatened, Mash begins his journey to becoming a \"Divine Visionary,\" a role so powerful that society would have no choice but to accept his existence.<br><br>And so, in order to maintain his peaceful life, the magicless Mash enrolls in the prestigious Easton Magic Academy, competing against the children of some of the most powerful and elite in the realm. Lacking the very skill needed to survive at Easton, magic, Mash appears to already be at a disadvantage to his fellow classmates. In order to achieve his goals, Mash will have to fight his way through every trial using his fists alone, overcoming magic with muscles, all for the illustrious title of Divine Visionary! [Written by MAL Rewrite]</p>'),('a2038ff4-4cd9-4244-8f15-d070e080dda9','b13e7a92-429f-4049-8985-fb1abbfa4161','\'Otome Game Sekai wa Mob ni Kibishii Sekai desu\' Reveals Additional Cast, Staff','2022-07-15 10:14:16','2022-07-15 10:14:16','62d13df85962b.jpeg','<p>The official website for the anime adaptation of Yomu Mishima\'s Otome Game Sekai wa Mob ni Kibishii Sekai desu (Trapped in a Dating Sim: The World of Otome Games is Tough for Mobs) light novel revealed an additional cast, staff, a new key visual (pictured), and a second promotional video on Tuesday. The series is scheduled to premiere on April 3 at 10:00 p.m. on AT-X, followed by TOKYO MX, Yomiuri TV, and BS Nippon Television.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Staff</p><p>Art Direction: Ryousuke Kawai (Tesla Note), Takamasa Nakakuki (Layton Mystery Tanteisha: Katri no Nazotoki File)</p><p>Art Design: Youko Nakao (Honoo no Labyrinth)</p><p>Color Design: Miho Hasegawa (Sakugan)</p><p>Director of Photography: Tomoyuki Ishiyama (Gegege no Kitarou (2018))</p><p>Editing: Yuusuke Ueno (Platinum End)</p><p>Sound Director: Takatoshi Hamano (Tsuki to Laika to Nosferatu)</p><p>Sound Effects: Yui Andou (Kami no Tou)</p><p>Music: Shou Aratame (Lord of Vermilion: Guren no Ou), Kana Hashiguchi (A3! Season Spring &amp; Summer)</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Akira Ishida (Mars Red) is voicing the spherical AI, Luxion.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Kazuya Miura (Kyuukyoku Shinka shita Full Dive RPG ga Genjitsu yori mo Kusoge Dattara) and Shinichi Fukumoto (Tantei wa Mou, Shindeiru. assistant director) are helming the anime at animation studio ENGI. Kenta Ihara (Ore dake Haireru Kakushi Dungeon) is handling the series composition and Masahiko Suzuki (Overlord II sub-character design) is designing the characters.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Mishima began penning the fantasy romance novel on the Shousetsuka ni Narou website in October 2017. Micro Magazine began publishing the series through its GC Novels imprint in May 2018. The ninth volume shipped on November 30.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>A manga adaptation by Jun Shiosato began serialization under Nico Nico Seiga\'s Dra-Dra-Dragon Age digital manga portal—now Dra-Dra Sharp#—in October 2018. Kadokawa published the seventh volume on January 8. The publisher\'s ComicWalker platform also serializes the manga.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Seven Seas Entertainment licensed the light novel and manga adaptation in English last April and December, respectively. The fifth novel volume shipped physically on March 8, with the fifth novel released digitally on January 20. The fourth manga volume will ship on April 19.</p>'),('a4477173-395a-4bb9-807c-89e01d03f0f6','d6de5dd8-df98-43dd-96a7-b3b9b713b62a','Anime Project of \'Isekai de Mofumofu Nadenade suru Tame ni Ganbattemasu.\' Light Novel in Progress','2022-07-13 12:24:57','2022-07-13 12:24:57','62ceb9998fbd6.jpeg','<p>The 13th volume of <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/49914/\">Himawari</a>\'s <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/manga/149114/\">Isekai de Mofumofu Nadenade suru Tame ni Ganbattemasu.</a> (I\'m Doing My Best to Make Myself at Home in Another World) light novel announced on Friday that an anime project for the series is in progress.<br><br>Himawari <a href=\"https://ncode.syosetu.com/n5077bk/\">originally began</a> writing the slice-of-life fantasy series on the Shousetsuka ni Narou website in November 2012. Futabasha began publishing the title through its M Novels f label with illustrations by <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/59618/\">Ran Kirou</a> in July 2016.<br><br>A <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/manga/114259/\">manga adaptation</a> by <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/31515/\">Yuriko Takagami</a> began on the <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/manga/magazine/1424/\">Monster Comics</a> website in November 2017. Futabasha shipped the ninth volume on April 28. The series has a cumulative 1.6 million copies of its light novel and manga volumes in circulation.<br><br>Synopsis<br>After a series of events, I received a gift from God and was reincarnated in another world! The super ordinary me fully enjoyed other world life while being watched over by my high-profile family. I spend my days fluffing and petting fantasy animals, thanks to the ability I received from God. There are also some dubious activities, but I\'ll do my best at various things with my cheat-like comrades while following God\'s lead!</p>'),('afd888f2-1c60-4fd7-8ab0-22f79c8bceca','d6de5dd8-df98-43dd-96a7-b3b9b713b62a','Manga \'Nokemono-tachi no Yoru\' Gets TV Anime','2022-07-13 12:33:29','2022-07-13 12:33:29','62cebb99603e6.jpeg','<p>Publisher Shogakukan opened an official website for a television anime adaptation of <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/53191/\">Makoto Hoshino</a>\'s <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/manga/132120/\">Nokemono-tachi no Yoru</a> (The Tale of the Outcasts) manga on Thursday and revealed a teaser visual (pictured above).<br><br>Hoshino serialized the fantasy manga in <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/manga/magazine/229/\">Shounen Sunday</a> from August 2019 to last year\'s April. Shogakukan shipped the eighth and final volume in May of the same year.<br><br>Seven Seas Entertainment licensed the manga in English in August 2020. The fifth volume shipped on June 28, and the sixth volume is scheduled to release on November 15.<br><br>Wisteria is an orphan girl living in a corner of the British Empire at the end of the 19th century. Her life is desolate and bleak–until she encounters Marbas, a powerful but equally lonely immortal being with a furry appearance, hounded by hunters. Together, Wisteria and Marbas roam the Empire–populated by humans and human-like beasts–in search of a place where they can live together in peace. (Source: Seven Seas Entertainment)</p>'),('b434c7a8-d5b6-4452-9677-708d2a0c0656','b13e7a92-429f-4049-8985-fb1abbfa4161','\'Komi-san wa, Comyushou desu.\' 2nd Season Reveals Supporting Cast, Promo','2022-07-15 10:18:31','2022-07-15 10:18:31','62d13ef7786db.jpeg','<p>The official website of the Komi-san wa, Comyushou desu. (Komi Can\'t Communicate) anime series revealed four supporting cast and the first promotional video for the second season on Wednesday. The new season will begin airing on April 7 at 12:00 a.m. on TV Tokyo, followed by TV Osaka, TV Aichi, and BS TV Tokyo. Netflix will exclusively stream the second season.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Cast</p><p>Makoto Katai: Shinichirou Kamio (Yakusoku no Neverland 2nd Season)</p><p>Shisuto Naruse: Katsuyuki Miura (SD Gundam World Heroes) NEW</p><p>Chuusaku Kometani: Shoutarou Uzawa (Jibaku Shounen Hanako-kun) NEW</p><p>Mikuni Katou: Fumiko Uchimura (Watashi, Nouryoku wa Heikinchi de tte Itta yo ne!) NEW</p><p>Ayami Sasaki: Minami Takahashi (Sentouin, Hakenshimasu!) NEW</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Note: The cast list includes voice actors that have been announced since the original news. The four new voice actors are denoted with legend NEW.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Voice actress Miku Itou (Adachi to Shimamura) is performing the opening theme \"Ao 100-iro.\" J-pop unit FantasticYouth (World Trigger 3rd Season) is performing the ending theme \"Koshaberi Biyori.\" The promotional video below previews both theme songs.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Kazuki Kawagoe (Koisuru Asteroid episode director) is returning to direct the second season at OLM, with chief director Ayumu Watanabe (Koi wa Ameagari no You ni). Deko Akao (Hitomi Mieno) (Hige wo Soru. Soshite Joshikousei wo Hirou.) is also returning to handle the series composition and Atsuko Nakajima (Sakamoto Desu ga?) is once again designing the characters.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The anime series adapts Tomohito Oda\'s school comedy manga, which he originally published as a one-shot in Weekly Shounen Sunday in September 2015. The magazine began serializing the manga in May 2016. Shogakukan published the 24th volume on January 18.</p>'),('c570c601-4684-468f-a64c-78a81f74a850','d6de5dd8-df98-43dd-96a7-b3b9b713b62a','Manhwa \'Solo Leveling\' Gets Anime in 2023','2022-07-12 07:45:15','2022-07-13 12:09:45','62ceb609d5c73.jpeg','<p>The <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/anime/producer/1468/\">Crunchyroll</a> Industry Panel at Anime Expo announced on Sunday an anime adaptation of <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/49667/\">Chugong</a>\'s <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/manga/121496/\">Solo Leveling</a> manhwa. The panel also revealed the main staff, teaser visual (pictured), and teaser promotional video. The anime is scheduled to premiere in 2023 on Crunchyroll.<br><br>Staff<br>Director: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/53467/\">Shunsuke Nakashige</a> (Megami-ryou no Ryoubo-kun., Sword Art Online: Alicization episode director)<br>Series Composition: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/2415/\">Noboru Kimura</a> (Kemono Jihen, Kyoukai Senki)<br>Character Design: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/40552/\">Tomoko Sudou</a> (Fragtime, Imawa no Kuni no Alice (OVA))<br>Music: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/8509/\">Hiroyuki Sawano</a> (86, Shingeki no Kyojin)<br>Studio: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/anime/producer/56/\">A-1 Pictures</a><br><br>Chugong began writing the action adventure series as a web novel on the <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/manga/magazine/1439/\">Kakao</a> website and was published by D&amp;C Media from July 2016 to March 2018 in 14 volumes. A webtoon adaptation drawn by <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/49668/\">Sung-rak Jang</a> began in Kakao in March 2018 and ended on December 29 last year.<br><br>Yen Press licensed the manhwa and web novel in English in August 2020 and shipped the fourth volume of the manhwa on May 10.<br><br>Synopsis<br>Ten years ago, \"the Gate\" appeared and connected the real world with the realm of magic and monsters. To combat these vile beasts, ordinary people received superhuman powers and became known as \"Hunters.\" Twenty-year-old Sung Jin-Woo is one such Hunter, but he is known as the \"World\'s Weakest,\" owing to his pathetic power compared to even a measly E-Rank. Still, he hunts monsters tirelessly in low-rank Gates to pay for his mother\'s medical bills.<br><br>However, this miserable lifestyle changes when Jin-Woo—believing himself to be the only one left to die in a mission gone terribly wrong—awakens in a hospital three days later to find a mysterious screen floating in front of him. This \"Quest Log\" demands that Jin-Woo completes an unrealistic and intense training program, or face an appropriate penalty. Initially reluctant to comply because of the quest\'s rigor, Jin-Woo soon finds that it may just transform him into one of the world\'s most fearsome Hunters. [Written by MAL Rewrite]</p>'),('d065ea6a-30c5-4fbc-ac5f-af9b64d8f625','d6de5dd8-df98-43dd-96a7-b3b9b713b62a','Manga \'Tomo-chan wa Onnanoko!\' Gets TV Anime for Winter 2023','2022-07-12 07:32:28','2022-07-13 12:10:00','62ceb618d77b8.jpeg','<p>The <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/anime/producer/1468/\">Crunchyroll</a> Industry Panel at Anime Expo announced on Sunday a television anime adaptation of <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/23483/\">Fumita Yanagida</a>\'s <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/manga/92149/\">Tomo-chan wa Onnanoko!</a> (Tomo-chan Is a Girl!) manga. The panel also revealed the main staff, cast, teaser visual (pictured) and teaser promotional video.The anime is scheduled to premiere in January 2023.<br><br>Cast<br>Tomo Aizawa: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/34785/\">Rie Takahashi</a> (Kanojo, Okarishimasu)<br>Junichiro Kubota: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/20156/\">Kaito Ishikawa</a> (Kakkou no Iinazuke)<br>Misuzu Gundo: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/5250/\">Rina Hidaka</a> (Kawaii dake ja Nai Shikimori-san)<br>Carol Olston: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/48349/\">Sally Amaki</a> (22/7)<br><br>Staff<br>Director: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/11268/\">Hitoshi Nanba</a> (Golden Kamuy)<br>Assistant Director: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/42429/\">Noriko Hashimoto</a> (High School Fleet)<br>Series Composition: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/46742/\">Megumi Shimizu</a> (Otome Game no Hametsu Flag shika Nai Akuyaku Reijou ni Tensei shiteshimatta...)<br>Character Design: Shiori Hiraiwa (Wonder Egg Priority 2nd key animation)<br>Music: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/7520/\">Masaru Yokoyama</a> (Fruits Basket 1st Season)<br>Studio: <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/anime/producer/1087/\">Lay-duce</a><br><br>Yanagida began writing the romantic comedy series on the Twi4 Twitter account and was published on the Saizensen website from April 2015 to July 2019. Kodansha released the eighth and final volume in September 2019. Seven Seas Entertainment <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/news/53555953\">licensed</a> the manga in English in February 2018 and released the eighth and final volume in September 2020.<br><br>Synopsis<br>Tomo Aizawa and Junichirou \"Jun\" Kubota are the tightest bros you\'d ever see. They roughhouse and spar, but through thick and thin, they\'ve got each other\'s back. Yet, there\'s just one small problem: Tomo is in love with Jun!<br><br>Since she was young, tomboyish Tomo has been just another one of the guys; due to his extreme muscle-brained nature, Jun doesn\'t notice any of her advances—not even when she explicitly confesses. To add insult to injury, for the longest time, he didn\'t even realize that she was a girl.<br><br>Tomo-chan wa Onnanoko! follows the comedic hijinks of Tomo and her friends as she tries to catch Jun\'s eye and escape the infamous brozone. [Written by MAL Rewrite]</p>'),('da22bd3b-43af-462d-8dba-eb457860b9a6','d6de5dd8-df98-43dd-96a7-b3b9b713b62a','Manga \'Isekai Shikkaku\' Gets TV Anime','2022-07-12 07:25:59','2022-07-13 12:10:24','62ceb630b230d.jpeg','<p>The official Twitter account of mangaka <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/40594/\">Takahiro Wakamatsu</a> announced a television anime adaptation of his and <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/people/43522/\">Hiroshi Noda</a>\'s <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/manga/122150/\">Isekai Shikkaku</a> (No Longer Human...In Another World) manga on Monday.<br><br>Noda and Wakamatsu began serializing the fantasy comedy manga on the <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/manga/magazine/1097/\">Yawaraka Spirits</a> website in October 2019. Shogakukan shipped the sixth volume on January 12, with the seventh volume is scheduled to be released on July 12.<br><br>Seven Seas Entertainment <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/news/66018126\">licensed</a> the manga in English on May 4 and will release the first volume this October.<br><br>Synopsis<br>An adventure in another world with cute girls by your side and video game-like powers–sounds like an anime fan\'s dream, right? Not so for melancholic author Osamu Dazai, who would quite literally prefer to drop dead. Video games haven\'t even been invented yet when he gets yanked into another world in 1948. Really, all the fantastical adventure he keeps running into is just getting in the way of his poetic dream of finding the perfect place to die. But no matter how much he risks his hide, everything seems to keep turning out okay. Follow a miserable hero like no other in this cheerfully bleak isekai comedy! (Source: Seven Seas Entertainment)</p>'),('fd055656-4f83-4d28-b82b-7523ad756dcb','d6de5dd8-df98-43dd-96a7-b3b9b713b62a','\'Birdie Wing: Golf Girls\' Story\' Gets Second Season in Winter 2023','2022-07-13 12:34:07','2022-07-13 12:34:07','62cebbbf5a9ad.jpeg','<p>The 13th and final episode of <a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/anime/50248/\">Birdie Wing: Golf Girls\' Story</a> announced on Wednesday that it is receiving a second season. The official website also revealed a teaser visual (pictured) and teaser promotional video. The anime is scheduled to premiere in January 2023.<br><br><a href=\"https://myanimelist.net/anime/producer/1258/\">Bandai Namco Pictures</a> produced the first season, which aired in Spring 2022. Crunchyroll simulcast the first season with subtitles as it aired in Japan.<br><br>Synopsis<br>Infamous among those who gamble on golf games, Eve uses her exceptional skill in the sport to earn a living—by betting and winning against various opponents. Known as the \"Rainbow Bullet,\" she vows to beat her foes and conquer the world of underground golf using only three clubs. However, the universe where Eve knows no defeat is shaken after she plays a clean game with Aoi Amawashi, a golfing prodigy that came to the country of Nafrece to enter a golf tournament. Armed with talent and born into the perfect environment for golf, Aoi the \"Innocent Tyrant\" calmly crushes her enemies with a bright smile on her face.<br><br>After their game-changing match, Eve and Aoi become intrigued with each other and promise to battle again someday. As Eve\'s aggressive and risk-taking approach challenges the elite and steady playstyle of Aoi, the two geniuses may just manage to bring golf to unexpected heights. [Written by MAL Rewrite]</p>');
